To Draw Out Toxins

The cult New York-based facialist Joanna Vargas injected a small bar of soap (1) with the hugely detoxifying properties of charcoal. Gentle enough for every day, it can be used on the entire body to deep cleanse and, thanks to olive oil and shea butter, hydrate.

For Super Soft Skin, in Two Steps

Long beloved for its versatile argan oil (to, most notably, hydrate the face and smooth hair), Kahina Giving Beauty has switched its sights to olive oil in crafting a just-released softening soap (2). Inspired by Moroccan hammams, it’s meant to be used as body mask: Apply head-to-toe after a steamy shower, and leave on for 10-15 minutes before removing with the brand’s new exfoliating glove (5).